2. Implement bubble sort using two pointers (start and end) and swapping adjacent elements if they are in the wrong order. We keep moving the start pointer forward until we reach the end.

```c++
void bubbleSort(Element *start, Element *end) {
    bool swapped = true;
    Element *ptr1 = start, *ptr2 = ptr1->next;
    while (swapped && ptr2 <= end) {
        swapped = false;
        while (ptr1 != ptr2) {
            if (ptr1->value > ptr2->value) {
                swapElements(ptr1, ptr2);
                swapped = true;
